            <title>[MAHOUT-1051] InMemoryCollapsedVariationalBayes0 to load input vectors with docIDs</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-1051</link>
                <project id="12310751" key="MAHOUT">Mahout</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Based upon our conversation with Jake in the user-list, I have modified the o.a.m.clustering.lda.cvb.InMemoryCollapsedVariationalBayes0.loadVectors so that it does not ignore document ids in input. To preserve backwards compatibility, it behaves as it did earlier if a ClassCastException is thrown; which occurs when ids are not integers, and/or the document vector (or getDelegate() if it is a NamedVector) cannot be cast to a RandomAccessSparseVector.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
